@node "Using_Finder" "Using Finder"
@next "Feedback_bugs"
@prev "Installation"

Finder is a CLI/shell tool, that examines if a given device/volume/assign
exists on your system. The argument template looks like this:

 NAME/M/A,DEVICES/S,VOLUMES/S,ASSIGNS/S,ALL/S

Where NAME is one (or several) entries you whish to look for. Remember though,
the names shall NOT have the trailing ':'!

DEVICES, when this one is set, Finder will ONLY look for devices. Volumes and
assigns are ignored. (Unless you set one of those as well). This is 
overridden by the ALL option. 

VOLUMES/ASSIGNS, the same goes for these as for DEVICES. Remember, 
VOLUMES/ASSIGNS/DEVICES may be combined. 

ALL, this options searches among all the different types. 

If no search-type is given, finder will default to ALL. 

Examples:

> Finder dh0 dh1 

Will search among devices,assigns and voulmes for dh1: and dh0:. 

> Finder DARTH ASSIGNS

Will search for DARTH: among assigns only. 


Finder will return 0 if everything was found correctly, 5 (WARN) if one (or several)
entries were missing, and 10 if an error occurred. 

@endnode

